==English==
====Etymology====
Latin [[linum]].
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-linen.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# (''[[uncountable]])'' Thread or cloth made from [[flax]] fiber.
# ''([[countable]])'' Domestic textiles made from linen or linen-like fabrics, such as [[tablecloth]]s, [[bedding]], [[towel]]s, and the such. 
#:''She placed the freshly washed linens into the linen closet.''
# (colour) A light beige colour, like that of linen cloth.
#:<table><tr><td>linen colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#FAF0E6" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>

